"docs.kde.org</ulink>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:381
#, no-c-format
msgid "&konqueror; the File Manager"
msgstr "Failihaldur &konqueror;"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:384
#, no-c-format
msgid "Folders and Paths"
msgstr "Kataloogid, kaustad ja otsinguteed"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:385
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In &UNIX; and &Linux; all folders are arranged in a simple hierarchy. "
"Starting from a top level folder (also called the root directory), the "
"structure descends and branches containing various files and subfolders. "
"This means that you can get from any folder to any other by going <quote>up "
"</quote> until you reach a common point then <quote>down</quote> through the "
"appropriate subfolders until you reach your target."
msgstr ""
"&UNIX; ja &Linux; korraldavad kõik kataloogid lihtsasse puukujulisse "
"struktuuri, mis hakkab allapoole hargnema ühestainsast ülemkataloogist. See "
"tähendab, et suvalisest kataloogist saab uude liikuda suunda "
"<quote>ülespoole</quote> võttes, kuni jõuab vastavate kataloogide ühise "
"punktini ja siis sealt <quote>allapoole</quote> liikudes vajaliku "
"alamkataloogini jõudes."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:392
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The position of any file or folder in the structure (also called a directory "
"tree) can be described by its <quote>path</quote>, which is a simple list of "
"the folders you would have to descend through to get to the target folder or "
"file. For example <filename class=\"directory\">/home/pam</filename> is the "
"subfolder <filename class=\"directory\">pam</filename> of the subfolder "
"<filename class=\"directory\">home</filename> of the top level folder, and "
"<filename>/home/pam/words.txt</filename> is the file <filename>words.txt </"
"filename> in that subfolder. The leading <quote>/</quote> in these paths "
"represents the top level folder."
msgstr ""
"Iga faili või kataloogi asukohta puus saab kirjeldada tema "
"<quote>otsinguteega</quote>, mis kujutab endast kataloogide loendit, mida "
"mööda on võimalik sihtkataloogi või -failini jõuda. Näiteks <filename class="
"\"directory\">/home/pam</filename> on ülemkataloogi kuuluva alamkataloogi "
"<filename class=\"directory\">home</filename> alamkataloog <filename class="
"\"directory\">pam</filename> ning <filename>/home/pam/words.txt</filename> "
"on selle alamkataloogi fail <filename>words.txt</filename>. Esimene "
"kaldkriips <quote>/</quote> toodud otsinguteedes tähistab ülemkataloogi."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:402
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Every folder accessible by your system &mdash; including those on other hard "
"disk partitions, a USB device or &CD-ROM; &mdash; will appear in the tree "
"descending from /, their exact paths will depend on how your system was set "
"up (see also the section on <link linkend=\"removable-devices\">Removable "
"Devices</link>)."
msgstr ""
"Kõik kataloogid, millele süsteem ligi pääseb &mdash; sealhulgas teistel "
"kõvakettapartitsioonidel, USB-seadmel või &CD-ROM;-il &mdash; on näha /-st "
"hargneval puul, nende täpne otsingutee sõltub sellest, kuidas süsteem on "
"üles ehitatud (vaata ka osa <link linkend=\"removable-devices\">Eemaldatavad "
"seadmed</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:407
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Every user on a &UNIX; / &Linux; system has their own <quote>home</quote> "
#| "folder to hold their personal files and settings; for example <filename "
#| "class=\"directory\">/home/john</filename> and <filename class=\"directory"
#| "\">/home/mary</filename>. The symbol <keycap>~</keycap> is often used to "
#| "represent the user's home folder, so that <filename>~/letter.txt</"
#| "filename> refers to the file <filename>letter.txt</filename> in my home "
#| "folder."
msgid ""
"Every user on a &UNIX; / &Linux; system has their own <quote>home</quote> "
"folder to hold their personal files and settings; for example <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/home/john</filename> and <filename class=\"directory\">/"
"home/mary</filename>. The symbol <keycap>~</keycap> is often used to "
"represent the user’s home folder, so that <filename>~/letter.txt</filename> "
"refers to the file <filename>letter.txt</filename> in my home folder."
msgstr ""
"Igal &UNIX; / &Linux; süsteemi kasutajal on oma kodukataloog ehk "
"alamkataloog <quote>home</quote>, kus on tema isiklikud failid ja "
"seadistused, näiteks <filename class=\"directory\">/home/juku</filename> ja "
"<filename class=\"directory\">/home/mann</filename>. Kasutaja kodukataloogi "
"tähistamiseks pruugitakse tihti märki <keycap>~</keycap>, nii et <filename>~/"
"kiri.txt</filename> viitab kodukataloogis olevale failile <filename>kiri."
"txt</filename>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:407
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Note that the term <quote>directory</quote> is often used instead of "
"<quote>folder</quote>."
msgstr ""
"Pane tähele, et sageli kasutatakse mõiste <quote>kataloog</quote> asemel ka "
"mõistet <quote>kaust</quote>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:411
#, no-c-format
msgid "View Modes"
msgstr "Vaaterežiimid"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:412
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In File Manager mode, &konqueror; lists which files and subfolders are "
"contained within a given folder and can provide you with some information "
"about them. The <quote>path</quote> of the current folder is shown in the "
"Location Toolbar. The way that &konqueror; displays the files and folders "
"depends mainly on your choice of view mode which can be selected from the "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>View</guimenu><guisubmenu>View Mode</guisubmenu></"
"menuchoice> sub menu. The view modes &konqueror; provides are outlined below."
msgstr ""
"Failihaldurina näitab &konqueror;, millised failid ja alamkataloogid "
"paiknevad antud kataloogis, samuti teatud teavet nende kohta. Aktiivse "
"kataloogi <quote>otsingutee</quote> on näha asukoharibal. See, kuidas "
"&konqueror; faile ja katalooge näitab, sõltub peamiselt valitud "
"vaaterežiimist. Seda saab valida menüüst <menuchoice><guimenu>Vaade</"
"guimenu><guisubmenu>Vaate režiim</guisubmenu></menuchoice>, kus on järgmised "
"valikud:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:422
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "In File Manager mode, &konqueror; uses an embedded &dolphin; component."
msgid ""
"In File Manager mode, &konqueror; uses an embedded &dolphin; component. "
"Please refer to the &dolphin; documentation for detailed information about "
"this mode."
msgstr ""
"Failihalduri režiimis kasutab &konqueror; põimitud &dolphin;i komponenti."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:425
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the <guibutton>Icons</guibutton> view, which is the default, files will "
"be represented by an icon that visualizes the file type, and a folder icon "
"will be shown for subfolders. The names of folders and files, and the items "
"enabled in <menuchoice><guimenu>View</guimenu><guisubmenu>Additional "
"Information</guisubmenu></menuchoice>, are displayed below the icons."
msgstr ""
"<guibutton>Ikoonivaates</guibutton>, mis on vaikimisi vaade, tähistavad "
"faile ikoonid, mis erinevad vastavalt failide tüübile, ning alamkataloogide "
"puhul näidatakse kataloogiikooni. Kataloogide ja failide nimesid ning "
"teavet, mis on lubatud alammenüüs <menuchoice><guimenu>Vaade</"
"guimenu><guisubmenu>Lisateave</guisubmenu></menuchoice>, näidatakse ikoonide "
"all."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:433
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <guilabel>Compact</guilabel> view shows the folder contents as icons "
"with the name beside it and the items enabled in <menuchoice><guimenu>View</"
"guimenu><guisubmenu>Additional Information</guisubmenu></menuchoice> below "
"the name. The items are grouped in columns similar to the <guilabel>Short "
"View</guilabel> in the &kde; file dialog."
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>Kompaktne</guilabel> vaade näitab kataloogide sisu ikoonidena, "
"mille kõrval on nimi ja selle all teave, mis on lubatud alammenüüs "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Vaade</guimenu><guisubmenu>Lisateave</guisubmenu></"
"menuchoice>. Elemendid on rühmitatud veergudesse nagu &kde; failidialoogi "
"<guilabel>lühivaate</guilabel> korral."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:441
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the <guibutton>Details</guibutton> view, the folder contents are "
"displayed as a detailed list which contains the name, size and last "
"modification time of each item. Additional columns can be added by clicking "
"a column header with the &RMB;."
msgstr ""
"<guibutton>Üksikasjade</guibutton> vaates näidatakse kataloogide sisu "
"üksikasjaliku loendina, mis sisaldab iga elemendi nime, suurust ja viimase "
"muutmise aega. Klõpsates veerupäisele &HPNga;, saab lisada muidki veerge."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:447
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "In the context menu of the header line you can choose between custom or "
#| "automatic column width. Automatic width adjusts the width of all columns "
#| "once to display the longest item in the column completely, except for the "
#| "<guilabel>Name</guilabel> column where the extension is replaced by "
#| "<quote>...</quote>"
msgid ""
"In the context menu of the header line you can choose between custom or "
"automatic column width. Automatic width adjusts the width of all columns "
"once to display the longest item in the column completely, except for the "
"<guilabel>Name</guilabel> column where the extension is replaced by <quote>…"
"</quote>"
msgstr ""
"Veerupäise kontekstimenüüs saab valida veeru kohandatud või automaatse "
"laiuse. Automaatse laiuse korral kohandatakse veergude laiust nii, et veeru "
"kõige pikem element oleks täielikult nähtaval, välja arvatud juhul, kui tegu "
"on veeruga <guilabel>Nimi</guilabel>, kus laiendi asemel näidatakse "
"<quote>...</quote>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:452
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The order of columns can be changed by drag and drop of column headers, "
"except for the <guilabel>Name</guilabel> header, which is always the first "
"column in this view."
msgstr ""
"Veergude järjekorda võib muuta veerupäiseid lohistades, välja arvatud veeru "
"<guilabel>Nimi</guilabel> korral, mis on selles vaates alati esimene."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:455
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The details view allows you to view the current directory in a tree-like "
"fashion if <guilabel>Expandable folders</guilabel> are enabled: Each "
"subfolder of the current folder can be <quote>expanded</quote> or "
"<quote>collapsed</quote> by clicking on the <guiicon>&gt;</guiicon> or "
"<guiicon>v</guiicon> icon next to it."
msgstr ""
"Üksikasjade vaade võimaldab näha aktiivset kataloogi puukujulisena, kui "
"lubatud on <guilabel>laiendatavad kataloogid</guilabel>, ning iga "
"alamkataloogi saab <quote>laiendada</quote> ehk avada, kui klõpsata selle "
"juures oleval <guiicon>&gt;</guiicon> või <guiicon>v</guiicon> ikoonil."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:464
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>Grouped View</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Rühmitatud vaade</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:470
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Grouped View</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Rühmitatud vaade</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:472
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"All view modes support grouping by the sort type selected in "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>View</guimenu><guisubmenu>Sort by</guisubmenu></"
"menuchoice>"
msgstr ""
"Kõik vaaterežiimid toetavad rühmitamist vastavalt sorteerimise tüübile, mis "
"on valitud menüükäsuga <menuchoice><guimenu>Vaade</"
"guimenu><guisubmenu>Sorteerimise alus</guisubmenu></menuchoice>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:479
#, no-c-format
msgid "Information in the View"
msgstr "Teave vaates"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:480
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In all view modes &konqueror; shows at least an icon and a name for each "
"item. Using <guisubmenu>Additional Information</guisubmenu> in the "
"<guimenu>View</guimenu> menu or the context menu of the header in "
"<guilabel>Details</guilabel> mode, you can select more information for each "
"item to be shown:"
msgstr ""
"Kõigis vaaterežiimides näitab &konqueror; vähemalt iga elemendi ikooni ja "
"nime. Menüü <guimenu>Vaade</guimenu> alammenüüga <guisubmenu>Lisateave</"
"guisubmenu> või päise kontekstimenüüga <guilabel>üksikasjade</guilabel> "
"režiimi korral saab lasta elementide juures näidata rohkem teavet."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:487
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guimenuitem>Size</guimenuitem>, <guimenuitem>Date</guimenuitem>, "
"<guimenuitem>Type</guimenuitem>, <guimenuitem>Rating</guimenuitem>, "
"<guimenuitem>Tags</guimenuitem> or <guimenuitem>Comment</guimenuitem>."
msgstr ""
